Branch A â€” What counts against the Crown
Institutional delay (e.g., crowded dockets, slow disclosure, waiting for forensic reports, scheduling gaps).

Crown-caused delay (late disclosure, overcharging, inefficiency, adjournments they ask for).

Investigative delay spilling into post-charge period (e.g., device seizures requiring long analysis that prevents trial from moving forward).

ğŸ‘‰ All of these are on the Crownâ€™s shoulders, not yours.

